        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-05-26T17:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-05-26T17:00:00-05:00" n="279" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d279">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.00112A EW/5–2645: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Ambassador in the United Kingdom</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Winant</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-05-26T18:00:00-04:00">May 26, 1945—6 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>4203. Please inform Missions in London Coordination Area<note n="36" xml:id="d279fn36">The London Coordination Area was composed of Ireland,
                        Sweden, Switzerland, Portugal and Spain with their possessions, Tangier,
                        Turkey, Iran, and Iraq.</note> that Confidential List will be abolished on
                    May 26 and suggest, where appropriate, that review of list be made for names
                    which should be promoted to Proclaimed List.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Grew</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
